# Per-machine override for tests/consumers.txt.
#
# Copy this file to tests/consumers.local.txt and edit. tests/consumers.local.txt
# is gitignored. If present, scripts/sync.sh and tests/run.sh use it INSTEAD
# of tests/consumers.txt — list only the consumers you actually have cloned.
#
# Same syntax as consumers.txt: one path per line. Comments start with #.
# Tilde (~) and ${VAR} expansion supported. Empty/comment lines ignored.
#
# Typical uses:
#   • member with only 1-2 consumers cloned — list just those, gate runs
#     green on the partial set without modifying the canonical consumers.txt
#   • machine with a non-standard checkout location (e.g. git worktree at an
#     unrelated path) — list the actual paths
#
# Per-repo CONSUMER_<name>=... env vars still work on top of this file and
# take highest priority.

# Examples (uncomment + edit):
#
# ${HYPEPROOF_WORKSPACE}/hypeproof-studio
# ${HYPEPROOF_WORKSPACE}/sediment
# /Users/me/work/hypeprooflab
